{{Quote|There were some Shard, however, that were still more persecuted than the rest, for they were a menace in yet another sense. For not only were they aliens, and not only were they droids, they were Jedi.|[[Tam Azur-Jamin]]|<ref name="Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena (article)">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/81/indexp7.html|text=Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena|int=Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena (article)}}</ref>}}
The '''Iron Knights''' were [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] [[Shard (species)|Shards]] that [[Jedi training/Legends|trained]] under the [[Sunesi]] [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Aqinos]]. Like all Shards, the Iron Knights required [[Droid/Legends|droid]] bodies to interact with the world, hence their name. They used [[Juggernaut war droid]]s, [[FLTCH-series battle droid]]s,<ref name="JATM">''[[Jedi Academy Training Manual]]''</ref> and [[Uulshos justice droid]]s as their hosts. Many Iron Knights took as their name that of [[Lightsaber crystal/Legends|lightsaber crystals]], reflecting both their connection to [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] and their crystalline bodies.

==History==
{{Quote|And an Iron Knight always follows orders!|An Iron Knight|<ref name="Star Wars Missions 14: The Monsters of Dweem">''[[Star Wars Missions 14: The Monsters of Dweem]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Iron_Knight_JATM.jpg|220px|thumb|left|An Iron Knight]]
Their first major appearance in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] was at the [[Arkanian Revolution]], where they assisted a team of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] sent by the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] to end the conflict. The [[Jedi Council/Legends|Jedi Council]], however, was horrified that Aqinos had taught inorganic crystals about [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], and felt that they could not truly understand the Force. Aqinos was excommunicated, and the Iron Knights went with him.<ref name="JATM" /> Many survived the [[Great Jedi Purge]] by hiding out on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Dweem]].

They were later discovered by a group of students from the [[New Jedi Order]], who put together clues provided by [[Callista Ming]]. After hiding out for 70 years, the Iron Knights were keen to rejoin the galaxy, and were accepted into the new Jedi Order without prejudice.

Iron Knights were on the front lines against the [[Yuuzhan Vong]], and [[Attack on Osarian|fought]] [[Attack on Uffel|on]] the planets [[Osarian]] and [[Uffel]]&mdash;against the [[Red Knights of Life]]&mdash;and reportedly even [[Attack on Kligson's Moon|saved]] [[Kligson's Moon/Legends|Kligson's Moon]]. When [[Hosk Station/Legends|Hosk Station]] was [[Battle of Kalarba|destroyed]], one Iron Knight, [[Luxum (Jedi)|Luxum]], was driven to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]].

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|I take no orders from you. So before I lop your head off, I have one question: be ye friend or foe of the Republic?|High Marshal [[Dragite (Jedi)|Dragite]]|<ref name="The New Essential Guide to Droids">''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Skipp_the_droid.jpg|200px|thumb|Skippy the Jedi droid, almost canonized as a Shard Jedi.]]
In the comic ''Jedi Academy: Leviathan'' there appears to be a droid sitting in the [[Jedi Praxeum]] cantina. When asked about this character on the [[Jedi Council Forums]], [[Abel G. Peña]] replied that "''the timing seems just about right, so I'd say that mug-of-something drinking droid is an Iron Knight, all right.''"<ref name="tfn1">{{JCFCite|url=posts/21494564|board=Literature|thread=TOS Exclusive Article: Droids and the Force|user=[[Abel G. Peña|Halagad_Ventor]]|date=2005-09-09|time=1:33 PM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801144435/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/tos-exclusive-article-droids-and-the-force.18701050/page-5}}</ref>

In an earlier draft of [[Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena (article)|''Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena'']], Peña had included an adventure seed where a group of Iron Knights went in search of Skippy, an [[R5-D4/Legends|R5-D4]] unit portrayed as Force sensitive in the Tales comic "[[Skippy the Jedi Droid]]." The explanation was to be that a Shard lived in the droid, but Peña felt the idea was "too warped" and so removed it from the final version.<ref name="tfn2">{{JCFCite|url=posts/18832600|board=Literature|thread=TOS Exclusive Article: Droids and the Force|user=[[Abel G. Peña|Halagad_Ventor]]|date=2005-03-19|time=11:49 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801144421/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/tos-exclusive-article-droids-and-the-force.18701050/page-3}}</ref>

